Employees are trained in manual discovery, emergency shutdown, evacuation and notification procedures in the highly unlikely event of a failure of the engineered safety and emergency systems.

The Plant does not require its employees to participate in conducting emergency response activities under the HAZWOPER standard; a “Non-responding Facility Policy” has been adopted for the Plant as a whole. In the event of an ammonia emergency, the response is to follow the procedures in the Equipment SOP’s and the California Hazardous Material Business Plan (HMBP). The overall procedure is to shutdown critical systems if it can be done safely by qualified personnel, evacuate, and notify the local response agencies and WPS; WPS employs technicians that are 1910.120(q) Hazardous Material Technician certified. Plant employees are to implement hazard communications, provide for the safety of visitors and report to the established Evacuation Staging Area(s) for a head count. Emergency response is coordinated with the City of Oxnard Fire/CUPA. Oxnard Fire/CUPA has confirmed that the facility is included in the Oxnard Community Emergency Plan required by the Emergency Planning and Community-Right-to-Know Act (EPCRA).  The CUPA is also welcomed to perform on-site emergency coordination activities annually.

